body:
I just ran into this weird failure in FIRRTL's Dedup pass:

```mlir
firrtl.circuit "Foo" {
  firrtl.module private @Bar(in %clock: !firrtl.clock) {}
  firrtl.module private @Baz() {
    %Bar_clock = firrtl.instance Bar @Bar(in clock: !firrtl.clock)
  }
  firrtl.module private @Qux() {}
  firrtl.module @Foo() {}
}
```

Running this through `circt-opt --firrtl-dedup` produces the following error:
```
error: 'firrtl.instance' op has a wrong number of results; expected 0 but got 1
    %Bar_clock = firrtl.instance Bar @Bar(in clock: !firrtl.clock)
                 ^
note: see current operation: %0 = "firrtl.instance"() <{
    annotations = [],
    domainInfo = [[]],
    layers = [],
    moduleName = @Foo,
    name = "Bar",
    nameKind = #firrtl<name_kind droppable_name>,
    portAnnotations = [[]],
    portDirections = array<i1: false>,
    portNames = ["clock"]
  }> : () -> !firrtl.clock
note: original module declared here
  firrtl.module @Foo() {}
  ^
```

